            <title>[HBASE-15468] why Hbase only split regions in one RegionServer</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15468</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I was writing 300GiB data to my Hbase table user_info, the table I created by default having only one region. When the writing was going I saw one region became two regions and more late on it became 8 regions. But my confusion is that the 8 regions were kept in the same RegionServer. Why Hbase didn&apos;t split the regions to different RegionServer. btw, I had 10 physical RegionsServers in my Hbase cluster, and the region size I set is 20GiB, Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
